-- Yen May Rise to Record 88.90 Against Euro This Year, Iwata Says
-- B y   M a y u m i   O t s u m a   a n d   A n d y   S h a r p
-- 2012-01-12T08:59:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/yen-may-rise-to-record-88-90-against-euro-this-year-iwata-says.html
A former  Bank of Japan  deputy
governor said the yen may rise to 88.90 against the euro this
year, topping the record high of 88.97 set on Oct. 31, 2000.  Speaking at a forum in  Tokyo  today, Kazumasa Iwata also
said the Japanese currency could weaken to 80 against the
dollar.  To contact the reporters on this story:
